    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-06T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-06T18:00:00-05:00" n="522"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d522">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 FEAC/10–645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Robertson</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="21" xml:id="d522fn1">Similar telegram sent to Moscow as
                        2104.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-06T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 6, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1625. Please deliver a note, the substantive portion of which should be as
                    follows, to the Generalissimo or the Minister for Foreign Affairs in your
                    discretion, referring to the Dept’s 1296, August 21, 8 p.m.:<note n="22"
                        xml:id="d522fn2">See footnote 28, <ref target="#pg_683">p. 683</ref>.</note>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In regard to the projected establishment of a Far Eastern Advisory
                            Commission, the Chinese Government is informed that the Government of
                            the United Kingdom has requested that India be included as a member of
                            the Commission and that the Secretary of State has indicated his assent
                            to the request. Does the Chinese Government concur in the inclusion of
                                India?”<note n="23" xml:id="d522fn3">China’s assent was sent October
                                22. India was invited on October 25 and accepted on October
                                27.</note>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
